revolt in the citadel; in Siwan the sun had an eclipse.
to Guzana; peace in the land.

in Arpad; defeat of Urartu made.
to Arpad, within three years taken.
to the foot of Mount Nal.
the king took the hands of Bel.
the king took the hands of Bel.
[the] nobles in Ellipa; [... ] entered his new house; [t]o Musasir.
to Bit-Zeri; the king stayed in Kish.
Sargon took the hands of Bel.
Kummuh conquered, governor appointed (var. nobles to Kummuh).
the king returned from Babylon; the chief vizier and the nobles, the booty of Dur-Yakin carried off, Dur-Yakin destroyed. On 22nd Teshrit, the gods of Dur-Sharruken entered their temples.
the king (stayed) in the land; the noble [...] in Karalla; on 6th Ayar, Dur-Sharruken completed; [...] received.
t[o...] Larak, Sarabanu, [...]; the palace of Kilizi was made; ... in [...]; the nobles against ...[...].

[As]hur-nadin-shumi, son of [Sennacherib]; [...] of the palace in the city [...] great cedar logs [...], alabaster in mount [Ammanana ...] in Kapar-dargil[i], ... to [...], [...] of the king ... [...].
